UNITED STATES of America, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. Rodrigo GUILLEN-HERRERA, a.k.a. Juan Martinez-Guillen, a.k.a. David Diaz, Defendant-Appellant. No. 06-14700

Non-Argument Calendar.

United States Court of Appeals, Eleventh Circuit. Feb. 21, 2007. Clarence W. Counts, Jr., Orlando, FL, for Defendant-Appellant. Roberta Josephina Bodnar, U.S. Attorney’s Office, Orlando, FL, for Plaintiff-Appellee.

Before DUBINA, BLACK and CARNES, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM:

R. Fletcher Peacock, appointed counsel for Rodrigo Guillen-Herrera, has filed a motion to withdraw on appeal, supported by a brief prepared pursuant to Anders v. California, 386 U.S. 738, 87 S.Ct. 1396, 18 L.Ed.2d 493 (1967). Our independent review of the entire record reveals that counsel’s assessment of the relative merit of the appeal is correct. Because indepen*854dent examination of the entire record reveals no arguable issues of merit, counsel’s motion to withdraw is GRANTED, and convictions and sentence are AFFIRMED.
